net.sf.sprockets.google

Class Places.Params

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.sprockets.google.Places.Params
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PlacesParams
    Enclosing class:
    Places

    @Value.Modifiable
public abstract static class Places.Params
extends Object

    Parameters for Google Places API services. Example usage: 

    Params.create().latitude(51.500702).longitude(-0.124576).radius(1000)
         .addTypes("food").keyword("fish & chips").openNow(true);

      • offset

        @Value.Default
public int offset()
        Zero-based position at which the previous characters in the search text should be used. For example, if the search text is 'Sprocke' and the offset is 4, then the search will be performed with 'Spro'. The offset value is typically the position of the text caret.

      • minPrice

        @Value.Default
public int minPrice()
        Lowest price level of places to search for. Valid values are from 0 (least expensive) to 4 (most expensive).

      • maxPrice

        @Value.Default
public int maxPrice()
        Highest price level of places to search for. Valid values are from 0 (least expensive) to 4 (most expensive).

      • openNow

        @Value.Default
public boolean openNow()
        True if only places that have specified opening hours and are open right now should be returned.

      • countries

        @Nullable
public abstract String countries()
        Country to search for places in. The value must be a two character ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 compatible country code, e.g. "GB". Currently only one country parameter is supported.

      • language

        @Nullable
public abstract String language()
        When searching for places, the language to return results in, if possible. If not specified, the default locale will be used.

        When adding a place, the language of the place's name.

        The value must be one of the supported language codes.

        See Also:
        Supported Languages

      • rankBy

        @Nullable
public abstract String rankBy()
        How the results should be sorted. Default value: RANK_BY_PROMINENCE.

      • pageToken

        @Nullable
public abstract String pageToken()
        Token for the next batch of results from a previous search. When this value is set, all other parameters are ignored.
